# Atlas CertOps
## Incident Response Plan

Version 1.0

Classification: Internal

---

# 1. Purpose

The Incident Response Plan establishes standardized procedures for responding to cybersecurity incidents affecting Atlas CertOps.

Objectives:

Minimize damage

Protect customer data

Restore service

Meet legal obligations

Preserve forensic evidence

---

# 2. Incident Severity

Severity 1

Complete outage

Confirmed data breach

Credential compromise

Ransomware

Severity 2

Partial outage

Major feature unavailable

Authentication failures

Severity 3

Minor degradation

Performance issue

Reporting issue

Severity 4

Cosmetic issue

Documentation issue

Minor UI defect

---

# 3. Incident Lifecycle

Preparation

↓

Identification

↓

Containment

↓

Eradication

↓

Recovery

↓

Lessons Learned

---

# 4. Incident Detection

Sources include:

System monitoring

Customer reports

SIEM alerts

Cloud provider alerts

Security researchers

Employee reports

Automated anomaly detection

---

# 5. Containment

Disable affected services if necessary.

Block malicious IPs.

Rotate credentials.

Disable compromised accounts.

Preserve forensic evidence.

Prevent lateral movement.

---

# 6. Investigation

Determine:

Attack vector

Timeline

Affected systems

Affected customers

Data exposure

Persistence mechanisms

---

# 7. Eradication

Remove malicious code.

Patch vulnerabilities.

Reset credentials.

Rebuild compromised systems.

Validate integrity.

---

# 8. Recovery

Restore services.

Verify functionality.

Increase monitoring.

Validate customer access.

Confirm security controls.

---

# 9. Communications

Internal notification

Executive notification

Customer notification (when required)

Legal notification

Regulatory notification

Public communication

---

# 10. Evidence Preservation

Collect:

Logs

Memory captures

Network captures

Database snapshots

Configuration history

Cloud audit logs

Evidence must remain unmodified.

---

# 11. Root Cause Analysis

Document:

Timeline

Root cause

Systems affected

Impact

Recovery

Lessons learned

Recommended improvements

---

# 12. Security Metrics

Track:

Mean Time to Detect (MTTD)

Mean Time to Respond (MTTR)

Mean Time to Recover

False Positive Rate

Incident Frequency

Severity Distribution

---

# 13. Incident Playbooks

Playbooks exist for:

Compromised Account

Credential Leak

Malware

Ransomware

Insider Threat

API Abuse

Privilege Escalation

Cloud Misconfiguration

Lost Backup

Data Corruption

---

# 14. Customer Data

Atlas CertOps follows these principles during incidents:

Protect customer confidentiality.

Notify affected customers when legally or contractually required.

Maintain forensic integrity.

Restore customer operations safely.

Document all actions taken.

